<br>
NWN's greatness isn't in the module it ships with, it's in the infinite possibilities it creates for DM and players all over.  I know I'll be pretty damn stoked if we can get some of the old crews together for gaming again once a week, like we did back in the day (80's and early 90's).  It won't even be an issue that we're scattered all over the US now, and we won't be confined to a linear story someone else is telling, our GM(s) can create their own now, and immerse us in it like never before.<br>
